grandma,
you were sugar and spice and everything nice. you were the gentlest and sweetest soul i have ever known. you went with me on my first trip ever out of the country for modeling and i will never forget how special that trip was and how you told me i looked beautiful when i shaved part of my head! i adore you. the glue of our whole family. 
every growing pain, 
every stint of homesickness,
every heart break, 
you were there. 
i used to search for my soulmate but there you were all along.
i’ll love you and miss you for the rest of my life. i’ll be seeing you.

sifting through all of my grandmas old photos with the help of my cousin we giggled and shed many tears. pinning together all her memories. i can feel her in all of these moments. whether it’s her going to prom, being small and silly with her sisters, welcoming new little cousins, falling in love, being with family. she was one of a kind. i just love these so much it makes my heart melt and break a little bit at the same time. i miss her so much. ❤️
